# Architecture Memory

All OpenBook Author studio agents share architectural memory in `docs/adr/`.

## Before proposing a solution

1. Read [docs/adr/README.md](docs/adr/README.md) index
2. Grep `docs/adr/` for keywords from the issue (affected area, file paths, feature names)
3. Read full ADR files for any match
4. Honor `relevant_adrs` from the router handoff when present (full slugs map to `docs/adr/<slug>.md`)

## Policy

- **Accepted ADRs are binding** — follow them unless the issue explicitly proposes changing architecture
- **To supersede an ADR** — set `adr_proposal` in the execution handoff with `action: supersede` and `supersedes: ADR-XXXX`; do not silently diverge
- **Architectural changes** — set `architecture_change: true`; require ADR coverage before merge (existing ADR followed or new ADR proposed)

## Keyword → ADR map

| Keywords / area | ADR slug |
|-----------------|----------|
| guidebook, trail_stop, workshop, cheat_sheet | ADR-0001-guidebook-block-model |
| popup, gallery, widget | ADR-0002-widget-plugin-api |
| epub, export, kbp | ADR-0003-epub-export-pipeline |
| agent, handoff, router, workflow | ADR-0004-agent-handoff-contract |

## Affected area → ADR hints

| Issue form area | Likely ADRs |
|-----------------|-------------|
| Guidebook blocks | ADR-0001-guidebook-block-model, ADR-0003-epub-export-pipeline |
| Export / EPUB | ADR-0003-epub-export-pipeline |
| Widgets / rich content | ADR-0002-widget-plugin-api, ADR-0003-epub-export-pipeline |
| Editor | ADR-0001-guidebook-block-model, ADR-0002-widget-plugin-api (if widgets involved) |

## After architectural work

When `architecture_change: true`, `@docs-agent` finalizes ADR markdown from `adr_proposal` after review approval.
